FBIS3-12883 "drnes044_j_94005" FBIS-NES-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Al-Bid Announces Halt to Media Campaign JN0703112294 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 7 Mar 94 p 24 JN0703112294 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Aden, QNA [Qatari News Agency]--'Ali Salim al-Bid, Yemeni vice president and leader of the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP], has announced a unilateral halt to what he termed vituperations and media campaigns, as of yesterday. In a message to the Yemeni people, broadcast over Aden Radio last night, al-Bid said the decision was made by the YSP Political Bureau in observance of the citizens' sorrow over the death of former Yemeni President 'Abdallah al-Sallal and out of respect for the last holy days of Ramadan. The vice president said in this regard: The decision, made under serious circumstances, reflected great sorrow over the death of Field Marshal 'Abdallah al-Sallal and our feelings about this mournful event.
